# mT5-small fine-tuning on the Ghana configs (Aka_Gha + Eng_Gha) — Colab T4 GPU.
# Reproduce: python src/train_generator.py --data-dir Data --output-dir generator_outputs \
#            --run-name mt5small_full --model-name google/mt5-small --epochs 2
#            (add --use-lora for the LoRA/PEFT variant)
# Real training artifacts: generator_outputs/<run>/history.csv, metrics.json, val_gen.csv, test_gen.csv

=== mt5small_full (FULL fine-tune, 300M params) — learning curve (history.csv) ===
step   25  train_loss=17.2096
step   50  train_loss= 5.4063
step  100  train_loss= 3.4271
step  250  train_loss= 2.7836
step  500  train_loss= 2.5260   | epoch 1 eval_loss=2.1943
step  750  train_loss= 2.3055
step 1000  train_loss= 2.2837   | epoch 2 eval_loss=2.0574
train_runtime=1537.99s  train_samples_per_second=10.42  total_flos=1.546e15
=> healthy convergence (20 -> 2.06), eval_loss <= train_loss at both epochs (NO overfit)

=== mt5small_lora (LoRA / PEFT, r=16, ~0.23% trainable params) — learning curve ===
step   25  train_loss=25.0987
step  100  train_loss= 6.4811
step  500  train_loss= 4.3471   | epoch 1 eval_loss=3.5225
step 1000  train_loss= 4.1785   | epoch 2 eval_loss=3.4093
train_runtime=1176.99s
=> converges but plateaus far higher than full FT (4.18 vs 2.28) — 0.23% params under-fit bespoke content

=== Verdict: generation vs retrieval (Val mean-ROUGE) — from metrics.json ===
subset    retrieval(beat)   mt5_full     mt5_lora     decision
Aka_Gha       0.356          0.3238       0.2704      keep RETRIEVAL (gen below)
Eng_Gha       0.332          0.3076       0.2233      keep RETRIEVAL (gen below)

INSIGHT: ~99%-unique Ghana answers mean retrieval returns real curated wording that
generation cannot reproduce token-for-token -> retrieval wins the 74% lexical metric.
Full FT > LoRA here (capacity matters for bespoke-content learning). Low loss did NOT
translate to high ROUGE: loss is a proxy, the metric is the judge. Generated answers are
fluent/on-topic (likely stronger on the 0.26 LLM-judge term) but lose on lexical overlap.
The per-subset Val gate therefore keeps retrieval, so submission_v5 == v4 (0.3701).
